We only need to determine the paid‑in capital from the “Initial” transactions. In our data the “Initial20231231001” rows are the owner’s contributions. They are as follows:
• Cash deposit: 5,000,000.0 
• Bank deposit: 15,000,000.0 
• Fixed Assets: 8,000,000.0 

Adding these together gives:
  5,000,000 + 15,000,000 + 8,000,000 = 28,000,000

Since there are no additional contributions or re‑classifications that affect paid‑in capital later on, the opening and closing (or end) paid‑in capital values remain the same.

Thus, the solution is:

{"solution": {"Paid-in Capital Initial Value": "28000000.00", "Paid-in Capital End Value": "28000000.00"} }
